tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE app_usage_statistics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    app_id INT,
    user_id INT,
    session_duration INT,
    action_type VARCHAR(50),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE app_usage (
    app_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    session_id INT,
    datetime TIMESTAMP,
    duration INT
);

CREATE TABLE app_analytics (
    analytics_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    app_id INT,
    event_type VARCHAR(50),
    event_time TIMESTAMP,
    user_action VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE ar_app_sessions (
	app_id UUID,
	session_id UUID,
	user_id UUID,
	session_start_time TIMESTAMPTZ,
	session_end_time TIMESTAMPTZ,
	session_duration INTERVAL,
	PRIMARY KEY (app_id, session_id)
);

CREATE TABLE ar_app_events (
	event_id UUID,
	app_id UUID,
	session_id UUID,
	event_type VARCHAR(50),
	event_timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ,
	event_data JSONB,
	PRIMARY KEY (event_id)
);

CREATE TABLE ar_app_performance (
	app_id UUID,
	cpu_usage FLOAT,
	memory_usage FLOAT,
	battery_level FLOAT,
	network_usage FLOAT,
	timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ,
	PRIMARY KEY (app_id, timestamp)
);

CREATE TABLE app_performance (
    performance_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    session_id INT REFERENCES app_sessions(session_id) NOT NULL,
    cpu_usage FLOAT NOT NULL,
    memory_usage FLOAT NOT NULL,
    network_usage FLOAT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE app_sessions (
    session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP,
    duration INT
);

CREATE TABLE app_performance (
    performance_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    session_id INT NOT NULL,
    cpu_usage FLOAT,
    memory_usage FLOAT,
    disk_usage FLOAT,
    network_usage FLOAT
);
